{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "They aim to segment texts into distinct units based on content rather than form or function.",
    "This is mainly conducted as a preprocessing step in automatic text summarisation to identify semantically coherent text sections, which are then summarised individually to acquire a final summary.",
    "Early work aimed to split texts into sections according to the different topics they addressed.",
    "This was first conducted by measuring the semantic similarity between sentences or paragraphs (Hearst, 1997).",
    "Subsequent work used techniques from topic modelling built upon Latent Dirichlet Allocation (Blei et al., 2003) to split the texts (Misra et al., 2011; Riedl & Biemann, 2012)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "This was first conducted by measuring the semantic similarity between sentences or paragraphs (Hearst, 1997).",
    "Subsequent work used techniques from topic modelling built upon Latent Dirichlet Allocation (Blei et al., 2003) to split the texts (Misra et al., 2011; Riedl & Biemann, 2012)."
